        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p> When moving to the Rocky Ridge community, you would want to know the demographics of the region to understand who your neighbours would be. As of the 2016 census, the Rocky Ridge population is made up of 8,195 private households with an income higher than the average income of the whole city of Calgary. The area is dominated by people in the age bracket of 15 to 64 years, and the majority of the residents are English speakers. Couples with children account for 52% of private households, couples without children account for 37% and lone-parent families account for 12%. </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Who would not want to enjoy scenic mountain views and comfortable living in an area surrounded by parks, schools, restaurants, cafes, and shopping centres? Potential residents looking for their dream house in an ideal location can choose from a wide range of house types in Rocky Ridge, including duplexes, apartments, rowhouses, and so on. Whether you need a large space for your growing family or a tiny space for you and your partner, Rocky Ridge's housing options will leave you awestruck.</p>
